==English==

===Etymology===
From the Latin ''mellitus'', honeyed/sweet + ''fluus'', flowing.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-mellifluous.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Flowing like [[w:honey|honey]].
# Sweet and smooth; generally used of a person's voice, tone or writing style.

